uise of ‘Santa Claus’ (an alteration of the Dutch form of his name, <i>Sinterklaas</i>)."],"variants":[{"name":"Nickolas","meanings":["Mainly U.S.: variant spelling of   Nicholas  , influenced by the short form   Nick ."]},{"name":"Nicolas","meanings":["From Late Greek.  See  <b>Nicholas</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705192,"age":0,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":9,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705195,"age":54,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Nicholas Hobart was born about 1328, in Bacton, Suffolk, England. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs. Nicholas Hobart. He was buried in Bacton, Suffolk, England."},"et":{"about 1328–":"umbes 1328–Surnud","1330–Female":"1330–Surnud","1354–1410":"1354–1410","1328–Male":"1328–Surnud","1337":"1337","about 1328":"umbes 1328","1410":"1410","1453":"1453","1354":"1354","1330":"1330","about 1354":"umbes 1354","1382":"1382","1328":"1328","Bacton, Suffolk, England":"Bacton, Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"about 1328–":"noin 1328–Kuollut","1330–Female":"1330–Kuollut","1354–1410":"1354–1410","1328–Male